etymologies: late 15th century: from Latin superscribere, from super- ‘over’ + scribere ‘write’

definitions: write or print (an inscription) at the top of or on the outside of a document

examples.text: they had superscribed “Top Secret” across the cover page

shortDefinitions: write or print inscription at top of or on outside of document

definitions: write or print an inscription at the top of or on the outside of (a document)

examples.text: he invariably will want to superscribe the memo with one of his banal mottoes

shortDefinitions: write or print inscription at top of or on outside of

definitions: write or print (a letter, word, symbol, or line of writing or printing) above an existing letter, word, or line.
shortDefinitions: write or print above existing letter or line
